# T1090.001 - IP Helper Service Proxy

## Author
Elad levi

## Description
Detects write operations to Windows PortProxy registry keys, which indicates creation or modification of port-forwarding rules used for internal proxying or lateral movement.

## Rule Class 
Registry

```tcl
Rule {
    Process {
        Include OBJECT_NAME {
            -v "*"
        }
    }
    Target {
        Match KEY {
            Include OBJECT_NAME {
                -v "HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\PortProxy\\**"
            }
            Include -access "WRITE"
        }
    }
}
```

## Tested Platforms
NA

## Notes
- Customers are advised to fine-tune the rule in their environment or disable the signature if there are false positives.

## References
